reviews.review_text:
Nobody for  President! Day two of this run from the Greek features some nice nuggets. The first set  opens  up with a  well played Music Never Stopped>Sugaree and although not   the strongest Sugaree, does get things off on the right  foot.

The first set continues to get better and  really hits it stride during Memphis Blues. A late set Far From Me is followed by an epic Birdsong, which as I  shared in my review for the  following show, has no midi effects and really showcases how strong a song this was for he band through out the 1980's.

Set  two starts off with a nominal version of China > Rider, which picks up steam toward the end.

LL Rain really shines and Jerry is now  completely dialed in. This  drops in a set high light Terrapin, which does suffer from from technical static from the radio broadcast toward the end.

The drumz this  night are quite  good and create this cool sonic soundscape that is quite enjoyable to listen to. The Space is nothing unusual and  is  loaded with Other One tease but gently drops into the west coast breakout of I will Take  You Home, which is warmly received.

Then it is off to the races with a high speed Other One, which raises the anti quite nicely and begins the race to the  finish line. A sweet Stella  blue is  followed by 
the Chuck Berry classic Around & Around then they rock it out and  blow the doors wide open with a set ending OMSN.

A poetic Knockin' on Heaven closes out this solid, if not typical for the period,show.

I would recommend listening to the radio broadcast filler, as it  gives you a cool  insight to those grand days of 1980's Grateful Dead, the days when the Dead owned it.
